The paper deals with data stream algorithms for testing codes, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The algorithms are designed to work in limited space, which is a characteristic of data stream algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from group testing, which is a problem in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The paper discusses error detection and tolerant testing, which are problems in cryptography (cs.CR) and coding theory (cs.DM), respectively.
